			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Casual player needing help<a name="67449"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 19 04 12:16 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I am thinkng you will be much happier starting out freash with eq2.  EQ1 has grown into a game that is not very friendly to those in your situation, and to spend too much effort this late in the game, for a game that is not user RL friendly, might be the wrong thing to do.
<br />

<br />
This game caters to the end game, if you are actually a main and not a twink, then it is a very awkward place to be.  At least a twink can buy their way somewhat, then again with no aa....we are talking about way too much time at this point.
<br />

<br />
EQ2 will level the playing field for you....no twinks,  and the game is a bit more RL friendly.  You can actually play for 2 hours and accomplish something.  Way too often 4 or more hours are required for eq1 and this is its biggest downfall for people such as yourself.
<br />

<br />
Choices are unlimited for some long timers, but very limited for others.  Even if it were a year ago, then maybe the time/fun factor would make staying with this game worth it....for now if it were me at 55 and no platinum or alts...I would be waiting for a new fresh start in the next eq.
<br />

<br />
Have fun, or as much as you can at this point, farming platinum for equipment is not going to be much fun though.  LFG is not much fun.  Swarming is the key to your sucess yes, but being 65 with the gear of a lv 40 twink is gonna make your life misserable.  The higher your lv gets the more you will notice just how tuff it is to be usefull to a group.....unless you do the painstaking job of farming to better your gear.  (skill ups might be low as well)
<br />

<br />
If all the hard core lifers stay with eq1 untill it dies, and all the &quot;casuals&quot; go to eq2 for the new game....well it might just make everyone much happier.
<br />

<br />
Lifers don't want a new start when they have 60% of their last 5 years of RL tied up into a game that is getting lamer by the day.  This is a bad scene for those who gave too much....they will be trapped here..at least you can go and really have fun in eq2:)  Perhaps you are the luckier of the 2.
<br />

<br />
Moose</span></td>
