				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Casual player needing help<a name="67451"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 19 04 12:19 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>At 54 I was swarm kiting the boats in Dulak and the campfire area in Nadox.   The cash drops were ok - usually  500ish pp an hour if I remember right.
<br />

<br />
Good upgrades for you would be the steel wrapped gear that droped in Ykesha.   The pieces sell for ~2k each (legs arms chest).   Also look at acrylia armor, the ac/hp/sta isnt too shabby for mid 50s' gear.
<br />

<br />
Steer clear of velious quested armor.   The reward is not worth the time investment, given the better alternatives.
<br />

<br />
Get into LDoN groups to build up points and wins.  Save up for the Mirigul and Tak armors.  The xp is still good there in the 50's, though the points are lacking.
<br />

<br />
I was wearing the Architects bejewelled BP until I got my 1492 pt BP from Tak this past weekend.   Yoiu can buy it for 8k max, usually on sale for less.
<br />

<br />

<br />
PoN Nightstalkers are good xp and cash if you can get the camp.
<br />

<br />
I would take time to learn swarm kiting on easier mobs though.   I learned back in iceclad on the giants there.   I then moved to GD elites, they were still blue up to the mid 50s easy, gave faction hits and were generally uncamped.
<br />

<br />
Once you can swarm the giants (loooonnng melee reach on them, uneven terrain on the plateau, and decent hit points) you can easily swarm nightstalkers in PoN, the boats in Dulak, or the trolls in Nadox.  All will get you past 60, and some decnt plat.
<br />

<br />
The adantage to swarm kiting is, aside from a drum, and a good wind instrument, you can kite nakid.
<br />

<br />
I would invest some time into LDoNs to get a wind instrument aug, and an item to put it on.   Not having to swap instruments to cast invis song is a huge bonus.
<br />

<br />
For 236 pts in Mistmoore you can have:
<br />

<br />
Gravestone of Dire Melodies 
<br />
Augmentation (Aug3) LORE NODROP Wind mod:1.6 (Rec lvl: 50)  BRD  
<br />
HEAD FACE EAR NECK SHOULDERS ARMS BACK WRIST RANGE HANDS PRIMARY SECONDARY FINGER CHEST LEGS FEET WAIST  
<br />
220  Mmc 
<br />

<br />
Nightrage's Ring 
<br />
Armor LORE NODROP (Rec lvl: 18) 
<br />
AC:+4 INT:+4 DR:+6 Slot1:type3  ALL  FINGER  16  Mmc
<br />

<br />
As an added bonus, there is a good chance you can get on one of your missions:
<br />

<br />
Trueborn Drum of Dark Rites  Percussion: 2.4
<br />
WT: 0.3  PRIMARY  Steward Omnivore and Steward Warden in Mistmoore Catacombs, Level 53 Normal Mission  
<br />

<br />
