				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Casual player needing help<a name="67484"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 19 04 2:37 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Normally I always tell people levels are more important than AAs.  However, for your situation I would suggest going 100% AA and getting 20 AAs.  Spend 3 on run 1/2/3 and 3 on regen 1/2/3.  When you hit 55 spend 2 on combat fury 1.  When you hit 63 buy Fade<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-14.gif" border="0" alt="Devil" hspace="2" />and Boastful Bellows (6).  The reason I say work on AAs now at 54 is you have a rare oportunity now that you won't have later on.  EQ gives a bonus to exp for mobs that are close to you in level.  The nightstalkers (werewolves) in PoN are 52 (iirc).  So you'll earn those AA at a decent pace.  Imo, the nightstalkers' exp really slows down once you hit 58.  You may be able to get over 60 there but your exp will really slow down.
<br />

<br />
I recommend those specific AA because they will set you up to be a good puller.
<br />

<br />
I'm in a similar type of guild though we are all mainly over 65.  Usually casual guilds have some people into tradeskills.  You may want to look into getting then to smith you some armor.  With all the drops in OoW all the prices have dropped alot in the bazaar...so do some bazaar hunting.  ONe thing that would really help you is a good drum.  I'd recommend the standard Thunderous Drum of Karanas (TDoK).  The TDoK should be realitively cheap though you may have to spend 4-5K depending on your server.  Since you have such a short time to play you will be soloing alot which means the drum is more important than upgrading your armor.  Don't bother with the Velious armor quests!  As the game has progressed that armor isn't adequate anymore.  That armor was good for it's time but PoP mobs are much tougher and hit alot harder than velious mobs.
<br />

<br />
Even though your time is limited try to group as much as you can.  At your level try for the PoN/PoD/PoI groups.  When you hit 62 try for BoT groups.  Most people expect bards to be the puller/mezzer, so hone your skills.
<br />

<br />
Later on as you get more pp try for the ornate boots as was earlier suggested and also get a Solstice earing (crafted - people sell a kit or you can buy the items in the bazaar).  Both of these items provide mana regen which will help in pulling (fade) and for swarm kiting.
<br />

<br />
Once you hit 64 and get your new charm song you can swarm the hobgoblins across the river in PoN or the Gargs in PoN.
<br />

<br />
Pyde Pypper
<br />
67+274</span></td>
