				<td colspan="2"><span>When I was at your level I use to Swarm PoN or PoD till i ran out of mana and go pull some LDoNs to &quot;med up&quot;.
<br />

<br />
 The Tak BP and all the rest in miragul armor is the way to go imho. If you dont have the Kunark Epic get it, You might need to wait for 56 like I did in order to be able to solo most of it (all but trak). Also, when I was leveling, I did 90% reg / 10% AA all the way. I ended up getting FM at 63 and thats pretty much the only AA you need. Once you got FM you can do Hard ldons easy and there is nice drops to get there.
<br />

<br />
The good side of being a bard is that the only gear you really need is the Kunark Epic, all the rest is just an add-on. You dont need gear to pull, you dont need gear to solo, it just help.
<br />

<br />
As for joining guilds, I owe LDoN to be Time/KT flagged. believe it or not, a lot of people lvl there alt in ldon and if you are a very good puller people start to notice you and talk about you. Thats how I got invited in one of the strongest guild of my server. Plus, you meet a lot of people with different guild tag, sooner or later you start to notice that some guild are better than others.
<br />

<br />
So, Solo while you have mana and get to know guilds and have them heard about you
<br />

