				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Casual player needing help<a name="67920"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 23 04 10:56 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>A friend of mine once told me something that saved my EQ life. I was getting stressed with leveling, could not find groups, all my friends were passing me, and I was about to quit. The advice he gave me was &quot;take it slow, at your own pace, and meet your goals, not theirs.&quot; Basicaly what this means, is solo when you have to, and don't try to overdo it. Set a reasonable goal for exp (20% maybe) and maybe even one for AAxp. Once you reach those goals, stop exping for the day. Do a quest, practice a tradeskill, sit and chat with some friends, just watch /ooc's in PoK. Exp grinds are generally no fun, and that is what EQ was intended to be about. On gear, make a GG char like a wizzy or druid, and sit in PoK watching for people offering for a GG or TL. Cash cow there. Hope this helps.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
