				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I am thinkng you will be much happier starting out freash with eq2.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
From all accounts so far, EQ2 blows and doesnt show any hope of being better. EQ2 is basically a worse game than EQ1 that takes double the PC to get half the frame rate. Slow leveling, cookie-cutter classes, gimped combat mechanics, and crappy FPS unless you have an UBER system. It doesnt even look that great IMHO. Not as good as WOW certainly.
<br />

<br />
WOW might be worth it for you, but personally I am in beta and I dont like it. It is a basically a single player MMOG. Grouping is actually discouraged by some game mechanics not to mention the game is way too easy. Items bascically fall off trees. The class interaction (and thus group tactics) are more limited than EQ. Think MMOG diablo.
<br />

<br />
The only MMOG worth playing in the future will be Vanguard. That's 2 years off, so there is PLENTY of time to ding 70 and get your epic 2.0 =)</span></td>
